    <h3>The Knuckle Huck</h3>
    <p>
        The snowboard knuckle huck, or simply "knuckle huck," is a thrilling freestyle snowboarding event that has gained popularity in recent years. 
        Unlike traditional snowboard competitions that focus on big jumps and halfpipes, the knuckle huck takes place at the transition between the 
        jump and the landing area, known as the knuckle. Riders aim to perform stylish and creative tricks while touching or "buttering" the knuckle 
        with their board. This event emphasizes innovation, flow, and technical skill, as riders showcase their creativity by linking spins, grabs, 
        and presses off the knuckle. The knuckle huck's relaxed atmosphere and emphasis on individual expression have made it a favorite among both 
        riders and spectators at snowboarding events around the world.
    </p>
